            <dt class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1E1B4B]">What grades is this site designed for?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#6B7280] leading-relaxed">The content covers grades K–5 (roughly ages 5–11), from basic 1-digit addition through 2-digit arithmetic, times tables, and division with remainders. The site is useful for any student who wants to build arithmetic fluency.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-5">
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1E1B4B]">How does progress tracking work?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#6B7280] leading-relaxed">Your scores, streaks, and session history are stored in your browser's local storage. Nothing is sent to a server — your data stays on your device.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-5">
            <dt class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1E1B4B]">What types of math can I practice?</dt>
            <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#6B7280] leading-relaxed">Addition (1-digit and 2-digit, with and without carrying), subtraction (1-digit and 2-digit, with and without borrowing), multiplication (mixed facts and times tables 1–12), and division (facts and division with remainders).</dd>
